      • getBackwardIterator

        public <InstanceType extends de.unisb.cs.st.javaslicer.common.classRepresentation.InstructionInstance> BackwardTraceIterator<InstanceType> getBackwardIterator(InstanceFilter<? super InstanceType> filter,
                                                                                                                                                      de.unisb.cs.st.javaslicer.common.classRepresentation.InstructionInstanceFactory<? extends InstanceType> instanceFactory)
        Returns an iterator that iterates backwards through the execution trace. This iteration is very cheap since no information has to be cached (in contrast to the Iterator returned by getForwardIterator(InstructionInstanceFactory). The trace is generated while reading in the trace file.
        Parameters:
        filter - a filter to ignore certain instruction instances. may be null.
        instanceFactory - a factory which is used to create the instruction instance objects. may be used to return special objects which can be annotated by the user of this function.
        Returns:
        an iterator that iterates backwards through the execution trace. the iterator extends Iterator over InstructionInstance.

      • getForwardIterator

        public <InstanceType extends de.unisb.cs.st.javaslicer.common.classRepresentation.InstructionInstance> ForwardTraceIterator<InstanceType> getForwardIterator(de.unisb.cs.st.javaslicer.common.classRepresentation.InstructionInstanceFactory<InstanceType> instanceFactory)
        Returns an iterator that is able to iterate in any direction through the execution trace. This iteration is usually much more expensive (especially with respect to memory consumption) than the Iterator returned by getBackwardIterator(InstanceFilter, InstructionInstanceFactory). So whenever you just need to iterate backwards, you should use that backward iterator.
        Parameters:
        instanceFactory - a factory which is used to create the instruction instance objects. may be used to return special objects which can be annotated by the user of this function.
        Returns:
        an iterator that is able to iterate in any direction through the execution trace. the iterator extends ListIterator over InstructionInstance.
